The paper deals with list-decodability of linear codes over a matrix space, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses techniques from coding theory (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CR) to establish its results. The paper may also be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG) due to the use of matrix spaces and linear codes.
